{{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Dogs: Their Fossil Relatives and Evolutionary History | title_orig = | translator = | image = Dogs Their Fossil Relatives and Evolutionary History.jpg | author = [[Xiaoming Wang (paleontologist)|Xiaoming Wang]] and [[Richard H. Tedford]] | cover_artist = | country = | language = English | series = | genre = [[Reference work|Reference]] | publisher = [[Columbia University Press]] | release_date = 2008 | media_type = | pages = 232 pp | isbn = 0-231-13528-9 | dewey= 599.77/2 22 | congress= QL737.C22 W36 2008 | oclc= 185095648 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Dogs: Their Fossil Relatives and Evolutionary History''''' is a book by [[Xiaoming Wang (paleontologist)|Xiaoming Wang]] and [[Richard H. Tedford]]. It was published in 2008 by [[Columbia University Press]]. The book offers a "holistic picture of canid evolution" and an overview of existing and extinct taxa, also detailing the evidence for the domestication and evolution of domestic dogs from their wolf ancestors.<ref>{{cite journal | last1=Lewis | first1=M | title=Dogs: Their Fossil Relatives and Evolutionary History | journal=The Quarterly Review of Biology | volume=84 | issue=3 | pages=315–316 | date=Sep 2009 | doi=10.1086/644718 | url=https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/644718?journalCode=qrb& }}</ref> It has received particular praise for its in-depth coverage of Chinese canids.<ref>{{cite journal | last1=Yule | first1=JV | title=Dogs: Their Fossil Relatives and Evolutionary History by X. Wang and R. H. Tedford | journal=Journal of Mammalogy | volume=90 | issue=2 | pages=525–526 | date=Apr 2009 | doi=10.1664/08-MAMM-R-282.1 | url=http://www.bioone.org/doi/full/10.1644/08-MAMM-R-282.1 }}</ref>
== References == {{reflist}}
[[Category:2008 books]] [[Category:Paleontology books]] [[Category:Zoology books]] [[Category:2008 in biology]]
{{evolution-book-stub}}

'''Energy in Syria''' describes [[World energy resources and consumption|energy]] and [[Electricity generation|electricity]] production, consumption and import in [[Syria]]. [[Energy policy of Syria]] describes the [[politics of Syria]] related to energy. The [[2011 Syrian uprising]] is an ongoing internal conflict in Syria.
Primary energy use in 2009 in Syria was 262 TWh and 12 TWh per million persons.<ref name=IEA2010>[http://www.iea.org/textbase/nppdf/free/2011/key_world_energy_stats.pdf IEA Key energy statistics 2011] Page: Country specific indicator numbers from page 48</ref>
==Overview==
