==Oil== According to [[BBC]] oil accounts for ca. 25% of Syria's income, estimated as $3.2bn for 2010. EU members account for ca. 95% of oil exports. Production was {{convert|400000|oilbbl/d|m3/d}} in 2009 and exports about {{convert|150000|oilbbl/d|m3/d}}, mainly [[Energy in Germany|Germany]], [[Energy in Italy|Italy]] and [[Energy in France|France]]. According to [[BBC]] oil reserves were 2.5bn barrels in 2010.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-14759416 EU steps up Syria sanctions with ban on oil imports] 2 September 2011 [[BBC]]</ref>
==Business== The [[Syrian Petroleum Company]] (SPC) is a state-owned oil company established in 1974.
