{{Taxobox | name = Viperinae | image = | image_caption = Asp viper, ''[[Vipera aspis]]'' | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Chordate|Chordata]] | subphylum = [[Vertebrate|Vertebrata]] | classis = [[Reptile|Reptilia]] | ordo = [[Squamata]] | subordo = [[Serpentes]] | familia = [[Viperidae]] | subfamilia = '''[[Viperinae]]''' | subfamilia_authority = [[Nicolaus Michael Oppel|Oppel]], 1811 }}
This is a list of all [[Genus|genera]], [[species]] and [[subspecies]] of the subfamily '''[[Viperinae]]''', otherwise referred to as viperines, true vipers, pitless vipers or Old World vipers. It follows the taxonomy of McDiarmid et al. (1999)<ref name="McD99">McDiarmid RW, Campbell JA, Touré T. 1999. Snake Species of the World: A Taxonomic and Geographic Reference, vol. 1. Herpetologists' League. 511 pp. {{ISBN|1-893777-00-6}} (series). {{ISBN|1-893777-01-4}} (volume).</ref> and [[ITIS]].<ref name="ITIS">{{ITIS |id=563898 |taxon=Viperinae |accessdate=23 March 2007}}</ref> For a full list of common names, see {{c|Viperinae by common name}}.
