{{Infobox artist | name = Mike MacDonald | birth_date = 1960 | known_for = Photography | notable_works = ''[[My Journey into the Wilds of Chicago]]'' | style = Immersive }}
'''Mike MacDonald''' (born 1960) is an American photographer, photojournalist, speaker, author and conservationist.<ref name=About>{{cite web |url=http://chicagonaturenow.com/mike-macdonald-photographer-conservationist/ |title=About Mike MacDonald |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2016 |website=ChicagoNatureNow.com |publisher=Morning Dew Press |access-date=June 21, 2016}}</ref><ref name=packard>{{cite book |last1=MacDonald |first1=Mike |last2=Packard |first2=Stephen |date=2015 |title=My Journey into the Wilds of Chicago: A Celebration of Chicagoland's Natural Wonders |location=Downers Grove |publisher=Morning Dew Press |page=13 |quote=(Foreword by Stephen Packard) |isbn=978-0-9963119-0-8}}</ref><ref name=Intl>{{cite magazine |last=MacDonald |first=Mike |title=Cover image |url=http://www.chicagonature.com/wp-content/uploads/published-work/Gardens-lllustrated-2009-Jan-COVER.pdf |magazine=Gardens Illustrated |location=United Kingdom |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=January 2009 |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> MacDonald's photos, primarily featuring prairies, savannas and other natural habitats around the [[Chicago metropolitan area]], are internationally published. MacDonald's original "hyper-real" photographic technique blends concepts from [[landscape photography|landscape]] and [[macro photography]] to create a three-dimensional, immersive effect in his work.<ref name=OutdoorPhoto>{{cite web |url=http://www.outdoorphotographer.com/how-to/shooting/land-and-sky.html#.V2q8UGgrKUm |title=Land and Sky: Tips for getting dramatic photos in the wide-open expanse of the American prairie|last=MacDonald |first=Mike |date=September 20, 2011 |website=Outdoor Photographer |publisher=Madavor Media |access-date=June 22, 2016}}</ref><ref name=WTTW>{{cite web |url=http://chicagotonight.wttw.com/2016/01/05/photographer-captures-wilds-chicago-new-book |title=Photographer Captures the ‘Wilds of Chicago’ in New Book |last1=Silets |first1=Alexandra |last2=Palmore |first2=Rebecca |date=January 5, 2016 |website=WTTW Website |publisher=WTTW |access-date=June 20, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Pete/> In 2015, MacDonald authored the acclaimed coffee-table book ''[[My Journey into the Wilds of Chicago]]''.<ref name=SunTimes>{{cite web |url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/chicago-prairie-wilderness-photography-book-mike-macdonald-interview/ |title=Sunday Sitdown: Photographer journeys to the ‘wilds of Chicago’ |last=Di Nunzio |first=Miriam |date=March 26, 2016 |website=Chicago Sun Times |publisher=[[Sun Times]] |access-date=June 22, 2016}}</ref><ref name=PW>{{cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-9963119-0-8 |title=Review: My Journey into the Wilds of Chicago: A Celebration of Chicago- land's Startling Natural Wonders |date=April 4, 2016 |website=Publishers Weekly |publisher=PWxyz, LLC |access-date=June 20, 2016}}</ref>
==Chicago nature== MacDonald's work primarily focuses on the natural habitats of the Chicago area. In 2015, MacDonald authored the [[coffee-table book]] ''My Journey into the Wilds of Chicago: A Celebration of Chicagoland's Startling Natural Wonders'', a collection built over two decades of more than 200 photographs and 30 profiles of Chicago area prairies, savannas, beaches and forests.<ref name=Trib>{{cite web |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/suburbs/downers-grove/news/ct-downers-grove-nature-author-0201-20160201-story.html |title=New book by Downers Grove resident offers look at area's natural gems |last=Ruzich |first=Joseph |date=February 21, 2016 |website=Chicago Tribune |publisher=Tronk |access-date=June 22, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'' called the book "''celebratory, soulful and poetic,''" and its photos "''glorious''."<ref name=PW/>
==Published works== {| class="wikitable" |- !Publication !Issue |- |''Outdoor Photographer''<ref name=OutdoorPhoto/> |1997-2011 |- |''Chicago Wilderness''<ref name=ChiWild>{{cite magazine|last=MacDonald |first=Mike |title=Cover image |url=http://midewinrestoration.net/?attachment_id=1504 |magazine=Chicago Wilderness |location=Chicago, IL |publisher=Chicago Wilderness |date=Summer 2002 |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> |1998-2009<ref name=Wilderness>{{cite web |url=http://midewinrestoration.net/?tag=chicago-wilderness-magazine |title=RIP Outdoor Illinois Magazine |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=March 6, 2012 |website=A Midewin Almanac |access-date=June 22, 2016}}</ref> |- |[[Water garden|''Water Gardening'']] |March/April 2002 |- |''Petersen's Photographic'' |October 1999 <ref name=Pete>{{cite magazine |last=MacDonald |first=Mike |title=Tips for Creating 3D Effects |url=http://www.chicagonature.com/wp-content/uploads/published-work/Petersens-Photographic-1999-Oct.pdf |magazine=Petersen's Photographic |date=October 1999 |access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref> |- |''Outdoor Illinois'' |April 2004 |- |''[[Boys' Life]]'' |June 2007 |- |''Garden's Illustrated'' |January 2009<ref name=Intl/> |}
==Notable work== *''[[My Journey into the Wilds of Chicago]]'', 2015, Morning Dew Press, {{ISBN|978-0-9963119-0-8}}, with forewords by [[Bill Kurtis]] and [[Stephen Packard]]
