{{See also|Glossary of ecology}}

The following [[Outline (list)|outline]] is provided as an overview of and topical guide to ecology:

'''[[Ecology]]''' &ndash; scientific study of the distribution and abundance of [[life|living organisms]] and how the distribution and abundance are affected by [[interaction]]s between the organisms and their [[environment (biophysical)|environment]].  The environment of an organism includes both physical properties, which can be described as the sum of local [[abiotic]] factors such as [[Sun|solar]] [[insolation]], [[climate]] and [[geology]], as well as the other organisms that share its [[Habitat (ecology)|habitat]].  Also called '''ecological science'''.

{{TOC limit|limit=2}}

