* {{annotated link|Biosphere}}

===Ecozone===

{{annotated link|Ecozone}}
The [[World Wildlife Fund]] (WWF) developed a system of eight biogeographic realms (ecozones):
* {{annotated link|Nearctic}} 22.9 mil. km² (including most of [[North America]])
* {{annotated link|Palearctic}} 54.1 mil. km² (including the bulk of [[Eurasia]] and [[North Africa]])
* {{annotated link|Afrotropic}} 22.1 mil. km² (including [[Sub-Saharan Africa]])
* {{annotated link|Indomalaya}} 7.5 mil. km² (including the [[Indian subcontinent|South Asian subcontinent]] and [[Southeast Asia]])
* {{annotated link|Australasia ecozone|Australasia}} 7.7 mil. km² (including [[Australia]], [[New Guinea]], and neighbouring islands).  The northern boundary of this zone is known as the [[Wallace line]].
* {{annotated link|Neotropic}} 19.0 mil. km² (including [[South America]] and the [[Caribbean]])
* {{annotated link|Oceania ecozone|Oceania}} 1.0 mil. km² (including [[Polynesia]], [[Fiji]] and [[Micronesia]])
* {{annotated link|Antarctic ecozone|Antarctic}} 0.3 mil. km² (including [[Antarctica]]).

